Comment: Vote game taking place over 14 months, from October of 2012 through December of 2013, played entirely by messages and diagrams on the bigpeta students club forum.  A very close game overall with neither side ever gaining a significant edge, the game swung to white in the endgame, perhaps beginning around move 34, and certainly between 34 and 42.
1...e5 received the majority vote.  Comments on 1...e5 vs 1...c5?
5. d4. setting up the open theme of the early part of the game.
5...Bxd4. black goes a pawn up here.  but white gains some running room.
8. Nc3.  three developed pieces plus a mobile queen for white to two and and a not so mobile queen for black.
8...h6.  keeping the knight unharried but watch what happens at move 12.
9. f4. placing a lot of value in open lanes, white opens things up in advance of a bold B for P exchange he'll attempt at move 12.
10...d6. still only two pieces out in play, this gives the bishop a path into the game.
